__nl__ So how do we develop the skills that we need ?
__nl__ Because it does take skill and practice , too .
__nl__ If we aren &apos;t going to be afraid of conflict , we have to see it as thinking , and then we have to get really good at it .
__nl__ So , recently , I worked with an executive named Joe , and Joe worked for a medical device company .
__nl__ And Joe was very worried about the device that he was working on .
__nl__ He thought that it was too complicated and he thought that its complexity created margins of error that could really hurt people .
__nl__ He was afraid of doing damage to the patients he was trying to help .
__nl__ But when he looked around his organization , nobody else seemed to be at all worried .
